# Deel Travel — product home task

## What's here

1. **Deel-Travel-Deck.pdf** — 16-slide presentation (landscape)
2. **Deel-Travel-Memo.pdf** — 3-page strategy memo (A4 portrait)
3. **Deel-Travel-Prototype.html** — clickable prototype, single HTML file, 6 screens

## Prototype navigation

Open `Deel-Travel-Prototype.html` in any browser. The left sidebar under "Travel" has six linked screens:

- **Overview** — dashboard with upcoming trips, PE-risk nudge, team on the road
- **Book a trip** — AI chat booking (conversational UX with inline policy and visa checks)
- **Flight search** — traditional search results with compliance badges
- **Booking review** — full trip detail with compliance panel and payment options
- **Approvals** — manager view with live PE exposure map
- **Reconciliation** — how the trip ties back to Deel Payroll and Deel Card

Clicks between screens work. The "New trip" button in the top-right takes you to the AI booking flow.

## Getting a shareable link for the prototype

Three options, 30 seconds each:

**Option A — tiiny.host (no account, instant)**

1. Go to https://tiiny.host
2. Drag `Deel-Travel-Prototype.html` onto the page
3. Copy the generated URL

**Option B — Vercel (free account)**

1. `npx vercel deploy Deel-Travel-Prototype.html` from terminal
2. Follow the login prompt
3. Copy the deployment URL

**Option C — Netlify Drop (free account)**

1. Go to https://app.netlify.com/drop
2. Drag the file onto the drop zone
3. Copy the generated URL

Any of these gives you a public URL to share in the submission.

## The thesis, one line

Deel should not fight Navan on booking. Deel should own the category no one else can serve: travel for the global, distributed, non-employee workforce. The distribution, compliance rails, and payment infrastructure are already built. Travel is the last missing Deel module.

## Key numbers cited

- Corporate travel market 2026: $1.5T (GBTA)
- 66% of spend unmanaged · 42% booking compliance
- SAP Concur market share: 49.6%
- Navan: 7,000 customers, $10B managed, $702M TTM revenue, 92% of revenue from supplier commission + interchange
- Deel: 35,000+ customers, $22B annual payroll, 150+ countries, 250 legal entities
- Deel Mobility launched March 2026 (visa + immigration, 100+ countries)
- Year 2 modelled revenue: ~$255M · ~80% gross margin
- Ring-fenced team ask: 30 people for FY26 · 90 days to beta
